Merge pull request #280 from K0den/firefox_mobile_browser_fix

Firefox mobile browser fix

Merge pull request #269 from fresham/package-json

Add package.json for dependencies

Add smoosh dependencies to Makefile

Setting the SMOOSH variable to the path of the binary allows us a
shorthand reference for use in a rule, listing as a dependency, and even
defining a target.

I've added a target so that if smoosh isn't there, make will actually
trigger NPM.

Then every target that used smoosh was changed over to use the $(SMOOSH)
variable (No more $PATH problem!) and given smoosh as a dependency.

Add package.json for dependencies

This allows contributors to easily install development dependencies via
npm install. The 'private' property prevents the project from being
listed as a package in the npm registry (as it is not actually
compatible with Node just yet).

Also added npm-debug.log to the project .gitignore so it does not get
tracked since it's just a by-product of npm.

This will probably also need jasmine and other dependencies as this is
just a foundation.

Also, note that since flotr2 is not yet Node-compatible, it should not
be installed or used as an npm package. We are simply leveraging the
dependency management features.

Built.

Expose selection object and fix for hit plugin when series out of
window.

Add selection object to select event.

This gives the developer access to the relative x/y positions of the
corners of the selection.  Necessary for axes other than the default
axis.  For #100.

Fix setting of closest

Fix the check for setting of closest to an actual hit.  A data series
may have positive length but be entirely out the window.  Fixes #91.

Built.

Fixes for tracking on multiple chart types and legend.  Performance
fixes for the scale.
Clear legend container div before drawing legend.  Fixes #96.

Fall back to default hit after exectueOnType

Fall back to the default hit if no hit is found on existing chart types.
I think this is sufficient but I could imagine it causing problems with
more esoteric hit implementations.  Also this will always prefer charts
with their own hit implementation over the default (lines).  We'll live
with this until implementing decisions for 'best' hit across multiple
chart types.  Fixes #92.

Scale by axis in chart type hit methods

Add the inverse scale method to the chart type API.  Use this to
translate mouse positions to coordinates in a particular series' scale
on chart type hit methods.  Fixes #93.

Switch to closure scales

Wow so binding was never meant to be a permanent solution, I just needed
a function for the charts API.  Lets use closures instead.  Now we are
faster.  Fixes #97.
declare variable n before using it

Built.

Fix for points fill style.  Fix for 84, points hit radius.  More robust
tracker positioning.

Points Hit Radius

I've added an over-ride for the points hit radius.  You can now apply
points : { hitRadius : 5 }, for example.  I'd like to make the hit
options more flexible in general but hopefully this can carry you until
then.  Fixes #84.

Centered Tracker Positions

Before, the relative tracker position only supported ne, nw, se, sw.
Now single n, s, e or w can be submitted and the tracker will be
centered in the other direction.

Points fillStyle fix

Apply the fillStyle option (calculated from series defaults, instead of
series color for fill.  Set opacity default to 1 for backwards
compatibility.  Opacity will now be applied.

Built

This includes fixes for 81, 82, 83, 86.  Also fixes HTML legend
background color and border.

Add preventDefault option

On mobile, preventDefault is required to disable scrolling.  This is
necessary for interactive functionality.  If not using interactive
features, the user can disable preventDefault.  Fixes #82.

Fix HTML legend styles

Make the default background color #F0F0F0.  Fix the application of the
border and background colors.

Fix z-index on legend BG

Setting the style directly wants 'zIndex'.  Fixes #81.

Check for bars / pie

Check for pie / bars before checking whether or not to draw the tracker
for that type.  Ultimately, this plugin should not be dependent on chart
types.  The chart types API should provide method for sensible
positions.  Fixes #83.

Merge pull request #88 from bmck/master

Tweak to setSelection
bug fix to place selection box in correct x-axis range on chart

Fix the back button.

Add a jQuery hashchange plugin and wire up to render examples or reset,
based on hash..

Spec for Mountain Nulls

Add a regression case for montain nulls.  Upgrade stable for passing
this test.

Allow Nulls in Mountain Chart

When filling the line chart we now handle nulls.  Instead of filling to
data[0], we now keep track of the start value to fill to.  When skipping
null values we conditionally fill the previous mountain.  After fill,
the path is reset.

Grouped bars support.

This is already supported, in theory.  We can draw bars and if the data
shows the bars as grouped, they will be grouped.  This implementation
makes the bars chart type aware of series, and in particular other
series when drawing.  I have not implemented hit suppoort (this presents
a similar coupling problem).

Right now, I'm leaning towards doing this with data preprocessing.  In
the current architecture, that preprocessing could be done with a plugin.
However, the drawback here is performance.  I'll think on this one more.
Let me know if you have any ideas.

Fixes #65.

Clip overlay context after hit

Add optional context parameter to clip method, defaulting to graph
context.  After drawing a hit, clip the overlay context.  Fixes #71.

Favor smaller bubbles in hit.

When calculating a hit on overlapping bubbles, favor the smaller bubble.
This is a simple heuristic for being fare when choosing a bubble to display
as hit. Fixes #72.

Fix hit when slice takes up entire pie.

In the case when a slices are zero, one slice may take the entire pie.  It
should allow hits on that slice.  Fixes #77.

Cast ticks to strings.

Ensure ticks are strings before proceding.  Tick formatters may return a
number.  We should not blow up because of this.  Fixes #75.

Add axis titles to divs.

Add flotr-axis-title-x1, -x2, -y1, -y2 classes to divs.  This lets HTML axis
titles be styled individually.  Simon, I am keeping the original classes for
compatibility. Fixes #79.
Calculate mouseX, mouseY per series.  Fixes #80.
